#month-banner("Three", "Seven", "The Peacock's Tail: Signs of Progress", "The iridescent threshold — Discernment and the discipline of honest observation")

#v(0.8em)

#hm-note[
  Month 7 opens Quarter III. The colour stage framework is the most
  diagnostically important teaching of Year Three because it gives the
  practitioner a reliable map of where their preparation stands. The most
  common error at this stage is premature claim of Albedo or Citrinitas.
  The long-work log is the cure: a practitioner who has been recording
  honestly cannot easily confuse two months of steady grey with the beginning
  of the whitening. Reinforce the observation protocols and the colour-matching
  discipline.
]

